    "title": "Opinion Announcement - May 24, 2012",
    "transcript": {
        "title": "Blueford v. Arkansas",
        "duration": 278.622,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 278.622,
                "byte_start": 107520,
                "byte_stop": 0,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 278.622,
                        "byte_start": 107520,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15086,
                            "name": "John G. Roberts, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_g_roberts_jr",
                            "last_name": "Roberts",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2730,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1127970000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2730"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32683,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 52305,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_g_roberts_jr_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 3702,
                            "identifier": "john_g_roberts_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.416,
                                "byte_start": 107520,
                                "byte_stop": 137195,
                                "text": "I have our opinion this morning in case 10-1320, Blueford versus Arkansas."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 7.416,
                                "stop": 13.758,
                                "byte_start": 137195,
                                "byte_stop": 162586,
                                "text": "The Double Jeopardy Clause, as a general matter, prohibits trying someone twice for the same offense."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.758,
                                "stop": 21.762,
                                "byte_start": 162586,
                                "byte_stop": 194664,
                                "text": "It has long been established, however, that a person maybe tried again if the jury could not agree on a verdict at his first trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.762,
                                "stop": 31.167,
                                "byte_start": 194664,
                                "byte_stop": 232281,
                                "text": "If a jury cannot reach a verdict, the judge declares what is known as a mistrial and the prosecution gets to decide whether to retry the defendant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.167,
                                "stop": 39.977,
                                "byte_start": 232281,
                                "byte_stop": 267494,
                                "text": "Now, in this case the State of Arkansas charged petitioner, Alex Blueford, with capital murder for the death of one-year-old child."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.977,
                                "stop": 46.781,
                                "byte_start": 267494,
                                "byte_stop": 294661,
                                "text": "That charge included the lesser offenses of first-degree murder, manslaughter, and negligent homicide."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.781,
                                "stop": 61.181,
                                "byte_start": 294661,
                                "byte_stop": 352340,
                                "text": "In other words, the jury could convict Blueford of anyone of those offenses depending on its view of the evidence and whether it thought the prosecution had carried its burden of proof on the particular elements that went with each offense."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.181,
                                "stop": 68.351,
                                "byte_start": 352340,
                                "byte_stop": 380970,
                                "text": "At trial, the court instructed the jury, when deliberating, to consider the offenses in order, from greater to lesser."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.351,
                                "stop": 78.239,
                                "byte_start": 380970,
                                "byte_stop": 420571,
                                "text": "Thus, the jury was told to begin with capital murder then if the jury had a reasonable doubt about whether Blueford was guilty of capital murder, to go on to first-degree murder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 78.239,
                                "stop": 84.1,
                                "byte_start": 420571,
                                "byte_stop": 443977,
                                "text": "Next, if the jury had a reasonable doubt on first-degree murder to go on to manslaughter, and so on."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.1,
                                "stop": 94.553,
                                "byte_start": 443977,
                                "byte_stop": 485773,
                                "text": "The court also presented the jury with a set of verdict forms which allowed the jury either to convict Blueford of one of the charged offenses or to acquit him of all of them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 94.553,
                                "stop": 98.984,
                                "byte_start": 485773,
                                "byte_stop": 503536,
                                "text": "Acquitting on some, but not others was not an option."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.984,
                                "stop": 104.402,
                                "byte_start": 503536,
                                "byte_stop": 525166,
                                "text": "After deliberating for a few hours, the jury reported that it could not reach a verdict."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.402,
                                "stop": 108.261,
                                "byte_start": 525166,
                                "byte_stop": 540630,
                                "text": "The court inquired about the jury\u0027s progress on each offense."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.261,
                                "stop": 120.945,
                                "byte_start": 540630,
                                "byte_stop": 591308,
                                "text": "The foreperson said that the jury was unanimous against guilt on the charges of capital murder and first-degree murder, was deadlocked on manslaughter, and had not voted on negligent homicide."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.945,
                                "stop": 124.443,
                                "byte_start": 591308,
                                "byte_stop": 605309,
                                "text": "The Court told the jury to continue to deliberate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.443,
                                "stop": 130.112,
                                "byte_start": 605309,
                                "byte_stop": 627984,
                                "text": "The jury did so but still could not reach a verdict and the court declared a mistrial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.112,
                                "stop": 133.403,
                                "byte_start": 627984,
                                "byte_stop": 641149,
                                "text": "The State subsequently sought to retry Blueford."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.403,
                                "stop": 138.878,
                                "byte_start": 641149,
                                "byte_stop": 663092,
                                "text": "Everybody agrees that he may be retried on charges of manslaughter and negligent homicide."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.878,
                                "stop": 145.043,
                                "byte_start": 663092,
                                "byte_stop": 687752,
                                "text": "The question is whether he may also be retried on charges of capital and first-degree murder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.043,
                                "stop": 158.024,
                                "byte_start": 687752,
                                "byte_stop": 739683,
                                "text": "Blueford says he can\u0027t be, because the foreperson\u0027s report that the jury was unanimous against guilt on capital and first-degree murder represented an acquittal on those charges."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.024,
                                "stop": 162.409,
                                "byte_start": 739683,
                                "byte_stop": 757238,
                                "text": "That report, however, was not a final resolution of anything."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.409,
                                "stop": 170.48,
                                "byte_start": 757238,
                                "byte_stop": 789525,
                                "text": "When the foreperson told the Court how the jury had voted on each offense, the jury\u0027s deliberations had not yet concluded."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.48,
                                "stop": 182.593,
                                "byte_start": 789525,
                                "byte_stop": 837904,
                                "text": "The jurors in fact went back to the jury room to deliberate further and nothing in the Court\u0027s instructions prohibited them from reconsidering their earlier votes as deliberations continued."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.593,
                                "stop": 193.11,
                                "byte_start": 837904,
                                "byte_stop": 880013,
                                "text": "The foreperson\u0027s report prior to the end of deliberations, therefore, lacked the finality necessary to amount to an acquittal on capital and first-degree murder."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.11,
                                "stop": 200.617,
                                "byte_start": 880013,
                                "byte_stop": 910002,
                                "text": "Blueford\u0027s other reason for why he can\u0027t be retried is that the trial court\u0027s declaration of a mistrial was improper."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.617,
                                "stop": 216.529,
                                "byte_start": 910002,
                                "byte_stop": 973740,
                                "text": "Blueford contends that there was no necessity for a mistrial on capital and first-degree murder given that the foreperson\u0027s report that the jury had voted unanimously against guilt on those charges meant that he had been acquitted on them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 216.529,
                                "stop": 227.521,
                                "byte_start": 973740,
                                "byte_stop": 1017626,
                                "text": "At that -- according to Blueford at that time, the court should have allowed the jury to give effect to those votes and then considered a mistrial only as to the remaining charges."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 227.521,
                                "stop": 237.362,
                                "byte_start": 1017626,
                                "byte_stop": 1057019,
                                "text": "But as permitted under Arkansas law, the jury\u0027s options in this case were limited to two, either convict on one of the offenses or acquit on all."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 237.362,
                                "stop": 249.711,
                                "byte_start": 1057019,
                                "byte_stop": 1106442,
                                "text": "The jury in this case was unable to do either and the trial court did not abuse its discretion by refusing to add another option, that of acquitting on some offenses but not others."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 249.711,
                                "stop": 256.767,
                                "byte_start": 1106442,
                                "byte_stop": 1134655,
                                "text": "The jury in this case did not convict Blueford of any offense, but it did not acquit him of any either."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 256.767,
                                "stop": 263.647,
                                "byte_start": 1134655,
                                "byte_stop": 1162136,
                                "text": "When the jury was unable to return a verdict, the trial court properly declared a mistrial and discharged the jury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 263.647,
                                "stop": 270.237,
                                "byte_start": 1162136,
                                "byte_stop": 1188571,
                                "text": "As a consequence, the Double Jeopardy Clause does not stand in the way of a second trial on the same offenses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 270.237,
                                "stop": 273.898,
                                "byte_start": 1188571,
                                "byte_stop": 1203200,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Supreme Court of Arkansas is affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 273.898,
                                "stop": 278.622,
                                "byte_start": 1203200,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Ginsburg and Kagan join."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
